South African Rugby has on Wednesday announced FlySafair as the new official domestic carrier for the Springboks and SA Rugby.FlySafair will carry the responsibilities and cater for SA Rugby domestic needs for the next three years. SA Rugby was recently sponsored by SAA but their sponsorship came to end in December 2016. As the official carrier of the springboks FlySafair will be responsible for ferrying the national team in all their official travels.Jurie Roux the CEO of SA Rugby says &#8220;we are absolutely delighted to partner with FlySafair and to welcome the airline to the rugby family,&#8221; he adds that Safair being in the aviation business for more that 50 years that see FlySafair as a new and modern player in the field.&#8221;Meanwhile FlySafair CEO Elmar Conradie said the partnership with SA Rugby means that they will be responsible for ensuring that the Springboks and their officials arrive to games on time, they are hopeful that the airline has the potential of achieving this. He added that the airline has been ranked as the most punctual airline in the country, this is according to stats published by ACSA.&#8220;It&#8217;s absolutely humbling to think that less than two and a half years ago we were a small airline with two aircraft operating between Johannesburg and Cape Town, and here we are today with a fleet of nine aircraft, servicing the largest domestic route network of all low-cost carriers, and receiving the honour of being entrusted with the air travel of one of our national treasures: the Springbok Rugby Team,&#8221; said Elmar Conradie.The partnership between SA Rugby and FlySafair was concluded at the OR Tambo International Airport on Wednesday where the official flight was unveiled with the Springbok logo on it.-TNA Reporter 